 A city under siege?  Chicago, the White House says, is under siege. Gang members and immigrants in the U.S. illegally swarm the city and crime is rampant, President  Donald Trump insists . National Guard soldiers are needed to protect government facilities from raging left-wing protesters. “Chicago is the worst and most dangerous city in the World,” he posted on Truth Social. The reality is far less dramatic . Violence is rare at protests, though angry confrontations are increasingly common,  particularly outside a federal immigration center  in suburban Broadview. And while crime is a serious problem, the city’s murder rate has dropped by roughly half since the 1990s.  



